\fs24 \cf0 \ulnone Napoleon Bonaparte, a Corsican by birth, one of the most brilliant individuals in history, Napoleon Bonaparte was a masterful soldier, and an excellent administrator. A product of the eighteenth century and was molded by ideas of the Enlightenment, wars and revolution at that time.\
This book \'93Napoleonic Revolution\'94 is about Napoleon who made a dramatic change in History specifically in France and Europe in a short space of time. A book about who this Napoleon is, what is in him that he was able to affect the history of mankind and how did he did these drastic changes. \
The book is written in first person point of view and in scholarly manner since it is a history book. The author seems very expert about the subject. The author of the book is Robert B. Holtman. He is a professor of History at Louisiana State University and received his doctorate from the University of Wisconsin. He can be considered as expert in this field and in this topic aside from his educational attainment because he has already written a lot of books related to this subject. Some are \'93The use of Propaganda\'94, \'93Napoleonic Propaganda\'94, and \'93The Era of the French Revolution\'94, and co-authored the book \'93The Correspondence of Catherine the Great with Germans on Current Political Affairs\'94. \
Robert B. Holtman emphasizes Napoleon's role as a revolutionary innovator whose influence touched nearly every aspect of European political and social life and has extended even to our own times.\'a0He discusses the whole aspect of Napoleon\'92s regime. From how does the Eighteenth century molded Napoleon\'92s whole being, him being a military genius, as an administrator, as an economist, as a catalyst of nationalism, and his legacy.\
His administration focuses mainly on centralization to seize more control of every aspect of the government. From institutions and organizations like the schools, economy, church, media, military and trade.\
The book is like a pocket book that has 225 pages with 10 short chapters. Contains European maps on 1789 the start of Napoleonic Era, 1812 the height of napoleon\'92s power with corresponding legend of his Allies, countries under his control and his enemies, and 1815 European map after the Congress of Vienna. It also has a chart of dates of Napoleon\'92s fights with his major enemies, chart of the organization of the Imperial University, and chart of the French government under the constitution of the year VIII. \
