\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 I.	The Heritage of The Eighteenth Century\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720\ri0\sl360\slmult1\sa200\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The first chapter talks about how the eighteenth century molded Napoleon Bonaparte. Events like rivalry of France and Great Britain, the Enlightenment, and the French Revolution became Napoleon\'92s background that made the time right for him. \
The enlightenment had very special features: a belief in natural law, a belief in reason so strong that whole century is sometimes called the \'93The Age of Reason\'94; a belief that the natural laws could be discovered through the use of reason; a belief that accompanying these natural laws were natural rights of man; a belief that through the use of reason and natural law of man could obtain a paradise on earth in the not-too-distant future; and belief in humanitarianism, that men were their brother\'92s keepers.\
The revolutionaries considered the Catholic Church as supernatural religion and unreasonable that is why they attacked the church that resulted to confiscation of the church lands, abolished monasteries, made the clergy as civil servants and the adoption of revolutionary calendar in an attempt to obtain more rational calendar than Gregorian. They applied the metric system and September 22 is the starting point of the calendar with 12 months (Vendemiaire, Brumaire, Frimaire, Nivose, Pluviose, Ventose, Germinal, Floreal, Praiarial, Messidor, Thermidor, and Fructidor), 30 days and each month is devided into 10 days and the days were designated by Roman numerals. This revolutionary calendar remains until 1806. \
Another revolutionary political bequest was the concept of written constitution. Each of the first three Revolutionary governments had a unicameral legislature because the \'93philosophes\'94, the publicist of the enlightenment, believed in popular sovereignty and thought a one-house legislature was the best way to express it. \
France at that time being strong-politically, militarily, and economically the strongest country in the continent-was significant for Napoleon\'92s career. This, then, was the background which made the time right for a Napoleon-the heritage of thought and events that start him on his way to greatness.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl360\slmult1\sa200\qj\partightenfactor0
